 while they search her body.  Well, the security guards' wand went off when checking her, even though she didn't have any metal on her, and they started hassling her, asking if she had any piercing or what not.  She told them no, of course, and by the time they let her go through the gate someone had gone through the bin she set her stuff in and took ALL 3 AIRLINE TICKETS as well as her personal info, drivers license and money.  She was livid.  The security guards didn't seem to give 2 shits that some random person had went through the bin and obtained 3 airline tickets.  WTF  I mean, isn't it the security guards' responsibility to watch over the bin that they said she HAD to put her stuff in?  Note that just a few days ago, a couple of terrorists had been caught when their names where pulled on a no fly terrorist alert.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=truthreason>TruthReason</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1383<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/14/03 5:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OMG Our airports are NOT safe, read this </span><hr size=1> Actually they are liable for those items that they take into custody....even if it means in a plastic basket on a conveyor belt which is subsequently moved to another location and went through. <br>
<br>
